ch.unige.ng.species
Class VectorIndividual<T>

java.lang.Object
  ch.unige.ng.species.AbstractIndividual<T>
      ch.unige.ng.species.VectorIndividual<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
Evaluable<T>, GlobalIndividual<T>, Individual<T>, Flushable, Copiable<GlobalIndividual<T>>, Poolable<AbstractIndividual<T>>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
public class VectorIndividual<T>
extends AbstractIndividual<T>
implements Flushable, Individual<T>

This implementation of the Individual interface is a basic linear fixed size individual where all the gene are instances of the same class. It uses an instance of Gene as prototype, using its newRandomInstance() method to populate the genome.

Version:
Suppression of genes.
Author:
Jean-Luc Falcone
